data.content:

&lt;p&gt;When copying an array in JavaScript to another array:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; arr1 = [&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;a&apos;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;b&apos;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;c&apos;&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; arr2 = arr1;
arr2.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;push&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;d&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);  &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;//Now, arr1 = [&apos;a&apos;,&apos;b&apos;,&apos;c&apos;,&apos;d&apos;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I realized that &lt;code&gt;arr2&lt;/code&gt; refers to the same array as &lt;code&gt;arr1&lt;/code&gt;, rather than a new, independent array. How can I copy the array to get two independent arrays?&lt;/p&gt;
